ContentBootstrap::AssignContextFamilies
  .call
    with occurrences that have senses with lexical_domain
      assigns correct context family based on lexical domain
    when selecting sense by MFS baseline (lowest sense_rank)
      assigns context family from MFS sense (lowest sense_rank)
      also sets sense_id on the occurrence
    with occurrences that have no sense (lexeme has no senses)
      skips occurrences whose lexeme has no senses at all
    with sense that has nil lexical_domain (fallback senses)
      assigns 'unknown' context family for nil lexical_domain
    with unmapped lexical_domain (adj.all, adv.all)
      assigns 'unknown' context family for unmapped lexical domain
    when run multiple times
      does not reassign on second run
    with multiple occurrences across domains
      assigns correct families for all occurrences
    when logging assignment counts
      logs summary with assignment counts

ContentBootstrap::AssignFallbackSenses
  .call
    with lexemes that have no senses
      creates fallback senses for all lexemes without senses
      creates fallback sense with correct definition for noun
      creates fallback sense with correct definition for verb
      creates fallback sense with correct definition for adjective
      creates fallback sense with correct definition for adverb
      creates fallback sense for lexeme with nil POS
    with lexemes that already have senses
      skips lexemes with existing senses
      does not create duplicate senses
    when run multiple times
      does not create duplicate fallback senses on second run
    with mixed lexemes (some with senses, some without)
      only creates fallback senses for lexemes without senses
    when logging
      logs summary with fallback count

