WordMastery::RecordCoverage
  .call with correct answer
    creates coverage records
    updates state with correct counters and percentages
  .call with incorrect answer
    does not create any records
  idempotency
    does not duplicate coverage on repeated call
  multiple senses coverage
    tracks coverage across different senses
  NULL sense edge case (FM-01)
    creates state and family coverage but skips sense coverage
  contribution creation (FT-034)
    creates a LexemeReviewContribution on correct answer
    does not create a contribution for incorrect answer
    is idempotent — second call does not create a duplicate contribution
    contribution_type (ASM-03 truth table)
      is new_sense_and_family when both dimensions are new
      is new_sense when only sense is new (family already covered)
      is new_family when only family is new (sense already covered)
      is reinforcement when both sense and family are already covered
    NULL dimension edge cases (NEG-02)
      treats NULL sense as already-covered and records new_family when family is new
      treats NULL family as already-covered and records new_sense when sense is new
    single-sense full coverage (NEG-01)
      produces 100% sense coverage with new_sense_and_family contribution

